        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 11:50PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 11509 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles west of Cut Bank, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cut Bank.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
